<br>
Execution is definitely the easiest under the condition you kill extremely quick each wave of mobs. Especially Execution raises a mana problem. As a mage, try to use 1-1.5 mana per wave and keep (depending on your mana pool of course) enough to Mala the Executionner, will help a lot. Though he CAN be nuked (I even critted an unresisted FoT on him, and that malaed, not malosinied), let the tanks/pets do the job. Your nukes are more needed in the 4 waves, as time is the key. For Exe, you have not to worry anymore about time.<br>
<br>
Under no circumstances should you heal your pet, even if it is epic, nor ask your local healer to do it. Mana, for everyone, must be rationned because of the key factor which is time at least in Exe. Keep a pet spell memmed, even if you are an epicced mage, because your pet will die and you need to be able to quick make a new one.<br>
<br>
Have a stack of star rubies for you. Banishment will be needed at some, not all, of the trials. The summoned mobs are those looking like rockfiends in the Grey, though not all &quot;rockfiends-looking&quot; mobs can be banished (etiher because they are too high, either because they are not summoned). Spend 200 mana by malosining before banishing, it really makes a difference. At level 61, I was never resisted on a Banishment when I malosinied before. Unmalosinied, I got some resists, and taunting factor of that kind of spell pretty high, he he ...<br>
<br>
Good luck and may the xp flow in your bars !<br>
<br>
<br>
Elemental Greetings<br>
