<br>
In a standard style group, I was using Shock of Fiery Blades, typically 2 shots per mob.  That meant as soon as the wave was over I was back in the corner resummoning pets at a feverish pace to regain mana.  Using this method I was never oom after the fourth wave.<br>
<br>
In an aoe group, I was obviously using Scintillation, typically about 3 times per wave.  That also meant I was resummoning pets for mana again betwen waves, but it was much easier than the standard group.  aoe is much more efficient.<br>
<br>
Fast mana regeneration and maximized efficiency are two of the biggest keys to doing the trials successfully.  Not everyone is on equal footing.  Choose your groupmates wisely. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ailees>Ailees</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ikebana-toulouse.com/maitres/ailees.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 817<br> <font color=#333333>(1/6/03 9:03:15 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm46.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=134.topic&index=32>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: AE group ?</span><hr size=1> I hope, Alita, that you know how canipet works ? <br>
